title: Uranium stocks extend gains as Trump signs orders to boost nuclear industry By Investing.com
summary: Uranium and nuclear technology stocks extended gains globally after U.S. President Trump signed executive orders aimed at boosting the U.S. nuclear industry. The orders are expected to increase demand for uranium and reactor technology, partly driven by the high electricity needs of the AI industry, where companies like Alphabet are funding nuclear energy agreements.

summary: The article summarizes key analyst rating changes and commentary on several AI-related stocks this week, including positive views on Nvidia, Tesla, Dell, and Bilibili, and a downgrade for MongoDB, based on their respective AI strategies and market positions.

title: Street Call of the Week By Investing.com
summary: The article summarizes several analyst stock calls from the past week, including a Wells Fargo downgrade of Reddit. This downgrade cited pressure on Reddit's user engagement and ad revenue stemming from Google's integration of AI-driven search features.

title: Four partners leave Paul Weiss following law firm’s deal with Trump By Reuters
summary: Four partners, including Google's lead attorney Karen Dunn, are leaving the law firm Paul Weiss to start a new practice. Their departure follows a recent deal between Paul Weiss and the Trump administration to lift an executive order targeting the firm.

title: Telegram ’surprised’ as Vietnam orders messaging app to be blocked By Reuters
summary: Vietnam has ordered telecommunication providers to block the messaging app Telegram, citing the company's alleged failure to cooperate in combating crimes and sharing user data. Telegram expressed surprise at the move, stating they have responded to legal requests and are processing a recent formal notice.

title: Oracle to buy $40 billion of Nvidia chips for OpenAI’s US data center, FT reports By Reuters
summary: Oracle reportedly plans to spend $40 billion on Nvidia chips to build a large data center in Texas for OpenAI, part of the US Stargate Project. This initiative aims to boost US AI capabilities, reduce OpenAI's dependence on Microsoft, and help Oracle compete with cloud market leaders like Google and Amazon.

title: Wedbush sets Street-high target on Tesla, calls it ’most undervalued AI play’ By Investing.com
summary: Wedbush Securities has significantly raised its price target on Tesla to a Street-high $500, reiterating an Outperform rating, based on the company's autonomous vehicle and AI strategy, which they believe is currently the "most undervalued AI play" with potential for massive future valuation creation.

title: Disney seeks to stop YouTube from hiring veteran to oversee sports and media By Reuters
summary: Walt Disney has filed a lawsuit against Alphabet's YouTube to prevent it from hiring veteran executive Justin Connolly, alleging breach of contract, unfair competition, and interference with his employment agreement which runs until March 2027. Disney seeks an injunction to stop Connolly from taking on his new role as YouTube's global head of media and sports, where he was appointed to oversee relationships and the growing live sports portfolio.

title: Google’s Youtube hiring former Disney exec Justin Connolly, sources say
summary: Sources indicate that YouTube, a division of Google (GOOGL), is reportedly hiring former Disney executive Justin Connolly. This move suggests YouTube is bringing in experienced leadership from a major media competitor.

title: Apple eyes 2026 smart glasses launch amid AI hardware race, Bloomberg reports By Investing.com
summary: Apple is reportedly accelerating development of AI-integrated smart glasses targeting a late 2026 launch, shifting focus towards this ambient computing wearable. This move is seen as a significant push into the competitive AI hardware market, where companies like Meta and Google (which recently announced its own AI glasses partnership) are also actively developing products.

title: Amazon tests AI audio summaries for products, expanding tech giant’s AI push (May 21) By Reuters
summary: Amazon is testing AI-powered audio summaries for products on its platform, analyzing details and reviews to provide highlights. This initiative is part of Amazon's broader strategy to integrate AI across its services, reflecting a wider trend among major tech companies.

title: Google faces DOJ probe over Character.AI deal, Bloomberg Law reports By Reuters
summary: The U.S. Justice Department is reportedly probing Alphabet's Google over its agreement with AI startup Character.AI, examining whether the deal violates antitrust law or was structured to avoid formal merger scrutiny. The probe is in its early stages and may not lead to enforcement action, according to the report.

title: Wall Street stocks end mostly flat in choppy trade as Treasury yields ease By Reuters
summary: U.S. stocks closed mostly flat after a choppy session, recovering initial losses as Treasury yields eased. The market digested the passage of a tax and spending bill while remaining cautious about ongoing concerns like tariffs and interest rates.

title: Treasury yields ease with US stocks flat to up; investors assess US tax bill By Reuters
summary: The article reports on fluctuating Treasury yields influenced by concerns over the U.S. fiscal outlook and a new tax bill, which eased later in the day after reaching highs. U.S. stocks ended flat to slightly higher overall, with the Nasdaq rising and tech stocks like Alphabet performing well, while some sectors like solar energy declined due to the tax bill's impact. The dollar strengthened, while commodities like oil and gold fell, and Bitcoin rose.

title: Stock market today: S&P 500 ends flat as US debt concerns weigh on sentiment By Investing.com
summary: The S&P 500 ended flat as market sentiment was pressured by concerns over high U.S. debt levels and the passage of a controversial tax and spending bill. Despite overall fragility, tech stocks, led by Alphabet, saw dip-buying and helped the market steady after a previous day's decline.
